20/06/2004
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Talks between Serbia-Montenegro and Macedonia on harmonising an agreement on minority protection were successfully completed in Belgrade on Friday (18 June). 
The accord would strengthen the rights of the Serbian minority in Macedonia and the Macedonian minority in Serbia-Montenegro.
In other news, both candidates in Serbia's presidential runoff have reportedly approached Bogoljub Karic for his support. 
Karic, one of the wealthiest people in Serbia, came in third during the first round. 
Boris Tadic of the Democratic Party is facing ultranationalist Tomislav Nikolic in the run-off. 
On Saturday, Nikolic said he would call early general elections if he is voted into office. 
(Tanjug, B92 - 19/06/04; Tanjug, Makfax, A1 TV - 18/06/04)
